    .article-text
      %h3
        Beach bag hacks
      
      %p
        These are my essential beach bag hacks.

      %p
        I regularly amend and upgrade this list with new ideas and items, but this is essentially my skeleton list that I adapt to wherever I am going and whatever type of trip I am on.
        These have never failed me yet.
        If you have any great hacks to share do let me know.
        I would love to share these on the blog and the best ones will get a top hack mention too. 

      %h4
        Plastic bag hack
      %p
        First I use this to keep my clothes clean and dry, and then I switch it out at the end of the day and use it for any rubbish I might have or my wet or sandy things like my beach towel.

      %h4
        Tissues
      %p
        Tissues can be an optional item, but I always remind myself that sometimes things get spilled or covered in stuff on the beach.
        So, a little handbag-sized pack is really good to have on standby.
        If you spill something in the sand it’s usually okay, but if you spill it on yourself, you are probably going to appreciate having a tissue in your bag.
        Let’s not forget the ice creams and soft drinks throughout the day.
        These are definitely sticky and messy in the sun.
        So, a small pack of tissues is going to save you from sun baked stickiness every time.

      %p
